# VOICE-GIS

VOICE-GIS is a voice-enabled geospatial mapping web application that allows users to interact with maps using voice commands. The project integrates speech recognition with GIS libraries like Leaflet/OpenLayers for an intuitive user experience.

## ğŸš€ Features

- ğŸ¤ **Voice Commands**: Zoom in/out, move to specific locations
- ğŸ—ºï¸ **Map Integration**: Uses Leaflet/OpenLayers for map rendering
- ğŸ”¥ **Real-time Updates**: Interactive and responsive interface
- ğŸï¸ **Optimized Performance**: Efficient map rendering with GPU/CPU optimizations

